### Story Challenges from 16th to 17th Jan

Explore  each of your 6  Alternativeku Story Ideas and decide on one to write: 

A. A man whose life is heavily controlled by a mysterious organization seeks to escape its influence, but his true goal turns out to be much deeper. 

B. Seeking a good life, an individual makes a bad choice with bad consequences. 

C. A man in a very bad place finds not only hope but also an unexpected feeling. 

D. A man whose childhood has marked his life finds something similar in his grown  -up children. 

E. A man finds the problem in his life is not what he thought it was. 

F. A man wants a million dollars, but he doesn't realize that the risk is higher than expected. 

Pick one option to write: Option B (Seeking a good life, an individual makes a bad choice with bad consequences.)

Now, write a short story of 400-500 words (2-3 minutes reading time)

```text
The man was looking for a good life.  When he turned twenty - one, he was fed up with his life and sought more.  The man was living in a two - story house , which was very chaotic.  The man's father was working at a job, earning about $300 a week, while his mother did not even have a job.

Since the man didn't have enough money to do anything exceptional, he turned to the easiest and most—attractive option: moving to the city.  Moving to the city would also allow him  to follow his dream and to continue with his studies. 

However, the man made no plans for his life after moving. He quickly moved through the days, each one more or less the same,  working a side  job and spending most of his time  thinking.  With this, he managed to earn  a few dollars,  but the days were getting  by, and his life was not improving as much as he thought.

One day, the man  realized that he needed more than this: he wanted to own a car, for example,  as well as  be in a  nice  place. 

But, in a  moment of weakness, the man considered  a  different option: he considered doing  some kind  of illegal work.  It seemed  that there  was  some money  to  be  made by doing something that  no  one  else  was  prepared  to do. 

At first, he made  some  money.  After  isolating  himself  from  most  of  his  former  friends,  he found himself  with more money than before.  However,  very  soon  he saw  that  there  was  a  problem:  he  was  becoming  involved  in  something much  bigger  than  he  thought  it  was. 

He  had  made  some  contact with the wrong  people, and these  people  were now accurately keeping a check on where he was and what he did to be   sure that   everything was going fine for them.

But  there  was  no   way  out:   he  had  gotten  into  illegal  business,   and   he  now   had   to  maintain  this  way  of life,   because   there   was   no  going  back.

