        -- Use the fact that the valuation is preserved under automorphisms.
        -- This is a fundamental property of valuations on fields.
        -- Here, we use the fact that the valuation is invariant under the automorphism `e`.
        -- We can use the `map` function to apply the valuation to `e x` and `x`, and since `e` is an automorphism,
        -- the valuation will be the same.
        -- This is a placeholder for the actual proof, which would involve showing that the valuation is preserved under `e`.
